# Commit & Branch Style

- **Conventional Commits**: `<type>(<scope>): <subject>`.
  - Types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `perf`, `docs`, `test`, `chore`, `build`, `ci`, `eval`.
  - Scopes match the work stream: `frontend`, `api`, `agents`, `memory`, `graphrag`, `mcp`, `infra`, `evals`, `safety`, `curriculum`.
- **Branches**: `feat/<stream>/<short-name>`, `fix/<stream>/<short-name>`, `eval/<stream>/<short-name>`.
- Keep commits small, atomic, and meaningfully named. Squash on merge unless preserving granular history is valuable.
- Reference the sub-agent brief in the PR description, not commit messages.
